          },
          "body": {
            "text": "The starts of Kladdragg, Cabragg and Sponken are on a fairly exposed ledge. Bring something (typically a cam) to anchor the belayer and avoid a tandem fall before the first bolt is clipped.\n\nThese routes and Borsten Torsten share a two-bolt top anchor that should be replaced or altered. The hangers sit a couple of centimetres proud of the rock, with around ten washers between them and the rock. Perhaps more seriously, the ring hanger in use is not connected to the other bolt. Instead, the chain has been attached to the expansion stud beneath it (meaning that if anything happens to it, the backup also fails...).",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-5.6-sol",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:beatelund"
            ]
          }
        },
